Description: Lower body sherd (mended from three fragments) of Milesian Fikellura pottery oinochoe; interior reserved; exterior, white slip: overlapping slim-petalled rosettes.
Curator's comments: The sherd probably belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1888,0601.556c and possibly belongs to the same vase as 1949,0516.15, 1949,0516.16, 1949,0516.18 and 1924,1201.1053. It ought to be pointed out that Cook (1933-1934, p. 43) also places 1888, 0601.556.b and 1888,0601.566.c into the group of 'Miscellaneous Oinochoai', unlike the other sherds cited above which are placed in the group entitled 'Zone Decorated Oinochoai Group'. The modern graffito ‘Diosk’ on the interior of the sherd indicates the findspot as the sanctuary of the Dioskouroi.
